OL,3,CStarmer leadership in peril as
OL,4,C'Cabinet ministers tell him to
OL,5,Cconsider position'
OL,7,FThe Prime Minister promised to prove
OL,8,Fhis "doubters" wrong at a press
OL,9,Fconference on Monday as former
OL,10,Fminister Catherine West withdrew
OL,11,Fthreats to imminently launch a
OL,12,Fleadership challenge.
OL,14,FBut his speech failed to quell demands
OL,15,Fthat he quit or set out a timetable
OL,16,Ffor his departure from discontented
OL,17,FMPs, who continued to call for his
OL,18,Fresignation.
OL,26,@pD@EOUpD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778547792
OL,3,CStarmer leadership in peril as
OL,4,C'Cabinet ministers tell him to
OL,5,Cconsider position'
OL,7,FMs West had previously said she would
OL,8,Fchallenge Sir Keir for the party
OL,9,Fleadership as early as Monday
OL,10,Fafternoon, in an attempt to force the
OL,11,FCabinet to put forward a replacement
OL,12,Fas prime minister.
OL,14,FAfter Sir Keir insisted he would not
OL,15,F"walk away", the former Foreign Office
OL,16,Fminister said she would now canvass
OL,17,Fsupport within the party for the Prime
OL,18,FMinister to set out a timetable for
OL,19,Fhis resignation by September.
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778547792
OL,3,CStarmer leadership in peril as
OL,4,C'Cabinet ministers tell him to
OL,5,Cconsider position'
OL,7,FPA understands that 80 MPs have signed
OL,8,Fa letter from Ms West urging Sir Keir
OL,9,Fto take this step, most of whom have
OL,10,Fpublicly expressed their loss of
OL,11,Fconfidence in his leadership.
OL,13,FMeanwhile, Joe Morris, a parliamentary
OL,14,Fprivate secretary (PPS) to Health
OL,15,FSecretary Wes Streeting, and Tom
OL,16,FRutland, a PPS to Environment
OL,17,FSecretary Emma Reynolds, Cabinet
OL,18,FOffice aide Naushabah Khan and Melanie
OL,19,FWard, a PPS to Deputy Prime Minister
OL,20,FDavid Lammy, all quit on Monday
OL,21,Fevening.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778547792
OL,3,CStarmer leadership in peril as
OL,4,C'Cabinet ministers tell him to
OL,5,Cconsider position'
OL,7,FDepartment for Work and Pensions aide
OL,8,FGordon McKee and Ms Mahmood's PPS
OL,9,FSally Jameson also left their posts
OL,10,Fhaving expressed a loss of confidence
OL,11,Fin the Prime Minister.
OL,13,FDowning Street did not immediately
OL,14,Frespond to the resignations, but
OL,15,Floyalist MPs David Burton-Sampson,
OL,16,FLinsey Farnsworth, Jayne Kirkham,
OL,17,FMichael Payne, Tim Roca and Sean
OL,18,FWoodcock were appointed to PPS
OL,19,Fpositions later in the evening.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
